```css
/* c-avatar component */
.c-avatar {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: var(--color-brand-500);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  overflow: hidden;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  /* No margin — Golden Rule */
}

.c-avatar__image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
}

.c-avatar__initials {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  pointer-events: none;
  user-select: none;
}

/* Size variants via data-state */
.c-avatar[data-state="small"] {
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="medium"] {
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="large"] {
  width: 64px;
  height: 64px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
}
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Fallback initials** — The `c-avatar__initials` element is always present but hidden via `aria-hidden="true"`. It sits absolutely positioned over the image. If the image fails to load or is absent, the initials become visible. This ensures a graceful fallback without JavaScript.

2. **Size via `data-state`** — Following MCSS state management rules, sizes are controlled by `data-state="small|medium|large"` on the root element. No class modifiers are used. This keeps the component consistent with the framework's state convention.

3. **No margin on root** — The `c-avatar` component declares no margin, adhering to the Golden Rule. External spacing is handled by layout classes (`l-stack`, `l-cluster`, etc.) wrapping the component.

4. **RDFa annotations** — The component is typed as `mcs:Atom` with a clear purpose. The image and initials are marked as `mcs:hasPart` for compositional clarity, even though this is an atomic component.

5. **Token-driven values** — All dimensions, colors, typography, and border-radius use `var()` references to design tokens. No magic numbers appear anywhere.

6. **Accessibility** — The initials element is hidden from assistive technology (`aria-hidden="true"`) since the image's `alt` attribute provides the accessible name. The component uses `overflow: hidden` and `object-fit: cover` to ensure the image fills the circular container cleanly.

# c-badge Component — Status Indicator

## HTML

```html
<span 
  class="c-badge" 
  typeof="mcs:Component" 
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays status indicators with semantic color states"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="none"
  data-mcs-consequence="visual status indication"
>
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Status</span>
</span>
```

## CSS

```css
/* ============================================
   Component: c-badge
   Layer: Component (c-*)
   Purpose: Status indicator with semantic colors
   ============================================ */

.c-badge {
  /* Layout — no margin (Golden Rule) */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);

  /* Visual */
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);

  /* Default state */
  background-color: var(--color-background-secondary);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);

  /* Transitions */
  transition: background-color var(--transition-fast), 
              border-color var(--transition-fast), 
              color var(--transition-fast);
}

/* Badge dot indicator */
.c-badge__dot {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: currentColor;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Badge label text */
.c-badge__label {
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  max-width: 12ch;
}

/* ============================================
   Semantic Color States
   ============================================ */

/* Success state */
.c-badge[data-state="success"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-success);
  color: var(--color-text-success);
  border-color: var(--color-border-success);
}

/* Warning state */
.c-badge[data-state="warning"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-warning);
  color: var(--color-text-warning);
  border-color: var(--color-yellow-500);
}

/* Error state */
.c-badge[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-error);
  color: var(--color-text-error);
  border-color: var(--color-border-error);
}

/* Info state */
.c-badge[data-state="info"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

/* ============================================
   Variant: Dotless (text only)
   ============================================ */

.c-badge--dotless .c-badge__dot {
  display: none;
}

/* ============================================
   Variant: Pill (larger, more prominent)
   ============================================ */

.c-badge--pill {
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
}

.c-badge--pill .c-badge__dot {
  width: 8px;
  height: 8px;
}

/* ============================================
   Variant: Outline (transparent background)
   ============================================ */

.c-badge--outline {
  background-color: transparent;
}

.c-badge--outline[data-state="success"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-green-800);
  border-color: var(--color-green-500);
}

.c-badge--outline[data-state="warning"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-yellow-800);
  border-color: var(--color-yellow-500);
}

.c-badge--outline[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-red-800);
  border-color: var(--color-red-500);
}

.c-badge--outline[data-state="info"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-brand-800);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

/* ============================================
   Accessibility: Reduced motion
   ============================================ */

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .c-badge {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* ============================================
   Accessibility: Focus visible
   ============================================ */

.c-badge:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-focus);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

## Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Default badge -->
<span class="c-badge" data-state="default">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Draft</span>
</span>

<!-- Success badge -->
<span class="c-badge" data-state="success">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Published</span>
</span>

<!-- Warning badge (dotless variant) -->
<span class="c-badge c-badge--dotless" data-state="warning">
  <span class="c-badge__label">Pending Review</span>
</span>

<!-- Error badge (pill variant) -->
<span class="c-badge c-badge--pill" data-state="error">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Critical Error</span>
</span>

<!-- Info badge (outline variant) -->
<span class="c-badge c-badge--outline" data-state="info">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">New Feature</span>
</span>
```

## Design Decisions

1. **No margin on root**: The `.c-badge` component declares no margin, adhering to the Golden Rule. Spacing is controlled by layout classes (`l-stack`, `l-cluster`) when badges are used in groups.

2. **Semantic states via `data-state`**: Following MCSS conventions, all state variations use `data-state` attributes rather than class modifiers. This ensures clean separation between structure (class) and state (attribute).

3. **Token-driven colors**: All colors reference design tokens (`--color-background-success`, `--color-text-success`, etc.), ensuring consistency with the design system and no magic numbers.

4. **Accessibility**: 
   - The dot has `aria-hidden="true"` since it's decorative
   - Focus-visible outline for keyboard navigation
   - Reduced motion support
   - Sufficient color contrast using semantic token pairs

5. **Variants as class modifiers**: Structural variations (dotless, pill, outline) use BEM class modifiers since they represent different visual structures, not states.

6. **Responsive text**: The label uses `text-overflow: ellipsis` with a max-width to handle long status text gracefully.

